# BatWise Cricket

## Overview
BatWise Cricket is a database-driven website focused on cricket bats for junior and adult players.  
The website provides information about different types of bats, along with a catalogue that displays available products.

This project is part of a coursework assignment to demonstrate the use of HTML5, CSS3, PHP, and SQL in building a content management system.

## Features
- Multiple linked web pages (Home, About Us, Shop, Contact, Login)
- Semantic HTML structure for accessibility
- Navigation system across all pages
- Member login area (to be developed)
- Database integration for storing cricket bat information
- Ability for members to add new bats (Part 2)

---

## Technologies Used
- HTML5
- CSS3
- PHP
- MySQL

---

## Project Structure

## Homepage Development

The homepage (index.php) has been developed using semantic HTML5 structure.  
It includes a header with a logo and site title, and a navigation menu linking to all main pages of the website.

The main content is organised into sections, providing an introduction to the BatWise Cricket website, information about junior and adult cricket bats, and an overview of the features available to users.

Accessibility principles have been considered by:
- Using semantic elements such as <header>, <nav>, <main>, and <section>
- Applying a clear heading hierarchy
- Including alternative text for images
- Adding a responsive viewport meta tag

The footer is included using PHP (`require_once`), allowing it to be reused across multiple pages and improving maintainability.

